q
/Tx BMC 
q
2 1 489.3312 305.999 re
W
BT
/HeBo 9.0 Tf 0 g
2 300.341 Td
(This SAR is being filed regarding suspicious activity involving Acme LLC, a medium-risk import/export business, which was discovered on March 5, 2026. The suspicious conduct involved a cash deposit of $901.00 made on the same day, which raised concerns due to its low amount, potentially indicating structuring behavior to avoid reporting thresholds. The transaction was completed, and the supporting documentation includes transaction records from Example Community Bank, where the account is held. The financial benefit from this transaction is unclear, as the origin and destination accounts remain unknown. The subject declined to provide an explanation for the large cash deposits, which raises further suspicion. There is no evidence of a cover-up or attempts to deceive regulators noted in the records. The activity took place at the bank's New York branch. Given the potential for money laundering and fraud, further investigation by law enforcement is recommended. No information was excluded from this report. Acme LLC has a history of prior SAR filings, indicating that this may not be an isolated incident. There is no related litigation currently identified, and the transaction involved U.S. currency. The bank's financial intelligence unit maintains all records related to this SAR.) Tj
ET
Q
EMC
Q

endstream
endobj
